<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-4043] thrift perl debian package is placing files in the wrong place</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-4043</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The libthrift-perl-0.10.0 package is installing things into /usr/lib, when it should be going into /usr/share/perl5.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This means &quot;Thrift.pm&quot; is being dropped directly into /usr/lib/Thrift.pm right now.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Ubuntu docker build environment, installing on Ubuntu 14.04 LTS&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
        <key id="13038454">THRIFT-4043</key>
            <summary>thrift perl debian package is placing files in the wrong place</summary>
